 SALIU SALIU HOODLUMS, on Friday night, attacked Government Science Secondary School, Kankara, in the Kankara Local Government Area of Katsina State. The hoodlums reportedly abducted many of the students of the ‘all boys’ boarding school. The bandits, who were said to have stormed Kankara town around 10.06pm on Friday, shot sporadically, and reportedly caused commotion in areas around the school. The attack on the school located in President Muhammadu Buhari’s home state, was executed on the same day the President arrived Daura for a week-long private visit, as announced by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, on Friday. The gunmen allegedly shot a security guard in the school in the attack. He was rushed to the hospital where he is currently receiving treatment, according to findings. It was gathered that only a quarter of the 800 students of the school were found. Many were abducted while some ran into nearby bushes for safety, sources said. Details later…  